    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Thanks, I'm sorry to say I never heard of SO_REUSEPORT, though it obviously makes sense for node app.\r\n\r\nI've just checked and found you are pretty correct - multiple server instances will serve grpc calls listening to the same port.\r\n\r\nAlso, if the port is taken by other appliction, the `Server.bind` returns `0` as you've described. Thank you very much! The only thing to regret is that documentation is lacking these details :)"
